.TH "t4_cfg_pfvf" 9 "t4_cfg_pfvf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t4_cfg_pfvf \- configure PF/VF resource limits
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t4_cfg_pfvf
.BI "(struct adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "unsigned int mbox "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int vf "  ","
.BI "unsigned int txq "  ","
.BI "unsigned int txq_eth_ctrl "  ","
.BI "unsigned int rxqi "  ","
.BI "unsigned int rxq "  ","
.BI "unsigned int tc "  ","
.BI "unsigned int vi "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cmask "  ","
.BI "unsigned int pmask "  ","
.BI "unsigned int nexact "  ","
.BI "unsigned int rcaps "  ","
.BI "unsigned int wxcaps "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
the adapter
.IP "mbox" 12
mailbox to use for the FW command
.IP "pf" 12
the PF being configured
.IP "vf" 12
the VF being configured
.IP "txq" 12
the max number of egress queues
.IP "txq_eth_ctrl" 12
the max number of egress Ethernet or control queues
.IP "rxqi" 12
the max number of interrupt-capable ingress queues
.IP "rxq" 12
the max number of interruptless ingress queues
.IP "tc" 12
the PCI traffic class
.IP "vi" 12
the max number of virtual interfaces
.IP "cmask" 12
the channel access rights mask for the PF/VF
.IP "pmask" 12
the port access rights mask for the PF/VF
.IP "nexact" 12
the maximum number of exact MPS filters
.IP "rcaps" 12
read capabilities
.IP "wxcaps" 12
write/execute capabilities

Configures resource limits and capabilities for a physical or virtual
function.
